 Description:
 Initial Spares/Repair Parts are required to fill the initial spares pipeline or repair parts inventory for all new aircraft systems, including modifications, support equipment, and other production categories. Initial
 spares/repair parts include peculiar repairable and consumable components, assemblies, and sub-assemblies that must be available for issue at all levels of supply in time to support newly fielded end items.

 The FY 2027 request for Initial Spares includes 1,441,052 thousand of discretionary and 1,132,293 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of 2,573,345 thousand. The FY 2027 funds are different from
 the FY 2026 mandatory funds the provided initial spares for F-16 squadrons, F-35 squadrons, Collaborative Combat Aircraft and Electromagnetic Warfare Aircraft. The FY 2027 mandatory provides initial spares
 for F-35 squadrons.

 The FY 2026 spend plan amount for Aircraft Procurement Initial Spares includes 1,193,535 thousand of discretionary and 1,030,740 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of 2,224,275 thousand.

 Initial spares are funded in the two program categories:

 1) Working Capital Fund (WCF) Spares category includes but are not limited to Readiness Spares Packages, New Acquisition Spares, Modification Spares, Support Equipment, Other Production, and
 Consumables. When the spares are delivered this central procurement account will reimburse the WCF. Since FY 1994, some programs have used obligation authority in the WCF to procure initial spares.

 2) Exempt Spares program category includes but not limited to Whole Spare Engines, Whole Spare Quick Engine Change Kits, Contractor Logistics Support, Simulators/Trainers, New Acquisition Spares,
 Modification Spares, Support Equipment, Classified Equipment, and Munitions. Exempt Spares are not purchased through the WCF. The budget authority is a direct cite on the contract.

