INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3010_L116$$, 2027, $$Funding is for the procurement of various Platform-in-a-Box (PIAB) and platform specific battlestation training equipment to include, but not limited to, hardware, software, licenses, peripheral equipment and
 sub-systems, visual display system, initial spares, install, and integration of those systems into the Joint Simulation Environment (JSE) battlespace. PIABs are the High-fidelity Operational Flight Program
 (OFP)-based, JSE-compliant/native simulators, featuring OEM-produced OFP-equivalent mission system & sensor software models capable of faithfully representing airborne platform performance. PIABs
 and battlestations will be used at various Joint Integrated Test & Training Center (JITTC) locations including but not limited to; Nellis AFB and Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, leveraging the JSE. PIABs
 and battlestations will support training operations, large force exercises, and local small force events. The intent is to replicate and expand the current digital test & training range capabilities allowing multiple
 dissimilar PIABs and battlestations to operate in a common environment without concern for airspace constraints, threat density, and outside surveillance, while protecting friendly capability Tactics, Techniques,
 and Procedures (TTPs) and future capabilities.

 Funding also procures the cockpits and interfaces to host Virtual Airborne Threat Solution - a virtual (operator-in-the-loop) threat representation capability enabling opposition force (OPFOR) to represent a
 broad selection of adversary aircraft based upon the particular test or training scenario. This capability incorporates Intel Center-developed, authoritative threat models with a USG-developed aircraft simulation
 architecture which enables aircraft capabilities and performance characteristics to be mapped to a single platform-agnostic cockpit and set of pilot-vehicle interfaces (PVI).

 JSE leverages 5th+ Generation Operational Test and Evaluation capability to improve TTPs in an operationally relevant environment. JITTCs support large force exercises and the United States Air Force
 Warfare Center, Weapons Instructor Course syllabus through Weapon School Integration. The high-fidelity simulator training to be provided by JSE improves the throughput capacity of Formal Training Unit
 and joint warfighter tactical readiness. Funding may also be used to address Diminishing Manufacturing Sources issues, obsolescence resolution and similar emerging requirements, as well as overarching
 programmatic support. This requirement (or modification) supports performance of a full financial audit as required by title 10 U.S.C. Chapter 9A, Sec 240-D. Funding for this exhibit is contained in PE 0207606F.

 Justification:
 Fiscal year 2027 Joint Simulation Environment (JSE) funds support the procurement of various Platform-in-a-box (PIAB) and platform specific battlestation entities to include, but not limited to, F-35, F-22,
 F-16, Virtual Air Threat System (VATS), and general hardware to support use of the PIABs and battlestations at the Joint Integrated Test & Training Centers. Funds also support the procurement of supporting
 battlestation hardware including but not limited to, control and reporting center, battle control center, and tactical operations center. JSE supports virtual training capability in support of joint warfighter readiness
 requirements across test, tactical, operational, and strategic levels. Funding in this PE invests in programs to meet Office of the Secretary of War and Chief of Staff of the Air Force initiatives to improve
 operational training against peer/near-peer threats for combat-coded operational units, as well as supporting High-End Advanced Tactics, Training, and Testing capability.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Air Force                                                                                                                Date: April 2026
