 support.

 -20MM Target Practice (TP) Round PGU-27A/B (AA24): This round is used for air-to-air and air-to-ground training in the M61A1/A2 gun systems installed on the F-15, F-16 and F-22 aircrafts. The cartridge is
 electrically primed and has no fuze. The projectile is a solid slug sized to match the ballistics of the PGU-28A/B. The PGU-27A/B is the primary ammunition used to provide a training capability to complement
 the PGU-28A/B high explosive incendiary combat round and ensure training is consistent with combat operations. Both the USAF and USN use this ammunition for training only. USN is the PICA and provides
 engineering support.

 -20MM PGU-39 (A931): PGU-39 is a dummy round that provides gun system training, aids in troubleshooting, and is utilized to verify M61A1/A2 gun system installed on the F-15, F-16 and F-22 aircrafts for
 readiness training and ensures weapon is cleared of any live rounds. Both the USAF and USN use this ammunition for training only. USN is the Primary Inventory Control Activity (PICA) and provides engineering
 support.
 -25MM Target Practice (TP), PGU-23/U (A978): 25MM PGU-23 is a target practice round used in the GAU-22/A gun system applicable to the F-35A aircraft. The round is a kinetic energy combat training round.
 Both the USAF and USN use this ammunition for training only. USN is the Primary Inventory Control Activity (PICA) and provides engineering support.

 -25MM PGU-48/B (AB98): PGU-48/B, Frangible Armour Piercing (FAP) 25MM, Combat Ammunition is a non-explosive, tungsten alloy kinetic energy penetrator in an aluminum non-discarding projectile body that
 is covered with a molded windscreen. The PGU-48/B (FAP) consists of a steel 25mm primed cartridge case (with primer and booster pellet), WC890 double-base propellant, and an inert projectile. This combat
 ammunition is used exclusively on the USAF F-35A Joint Strike Fighter (JSF). USAF is the PICA and provides engineering support.


