INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3080_L027$$, 2027, $$Cheyenne Mountain Complex (CMC) systems provide real-time ballistic missile warning, air defense, force management, battle management and command, control and communications for the North American
 Air Defense (NORAD) missions.

 PE 0305903F - Mobile Command and Control System (MC2S)

 Modification for the COMBATANT COMMANDER (CCDR), Mobile Command and Control System (MC2S); The CCDR's MC2S provides command capabilities to accomplish directed missions in the event of a
 national level emergency. It provides resilient command, control, communications, computers, and intelligence (C4I) capability accomplishing directed COCOM missions. The MC2S provides C4I for Homeland
 Support/Homeland Defense (HLS/HLD) and U.S. Northern Command (USNORTHCOM).

 MC2S Mod 08 Block 06 will execute MC2S Block 06 modifications which include but are not limited to: 1) Communication system upgrades; 2) Mission and support asset upgrades; 3) Cyber security
 modernization; 4) Network upgrades; 5) Environmental and Filtration system upgrades along with and including initial spares and test facility updates required by the fielding of these modifications. FY26 increase
 is funding efforts to include Integrated Base Defense Security System (IBDSS) which is a replacement of security system components (intrusion detection system, access control system, closed-circuit television
 system, annunciator, cameras, sensors) for the MC2S in-garrison location at the 253 CACG on F.E. Warren AFB and a funding increase for classified effort and can be addressed via proper classification
 channels. Decrease to FY27 levels is a return to baseline funding profile.

 MC2S Mod 09 Block 07 will execute MC2S Block 07 modifications which include but are not limited to: 1) Communication system upgrades; 2) Mission and support asset upgrades; 3) Cyber security
 modernization; 4) Network upgrades; 5) Environmental and Filtration system upgrades along with and including initial spares and test facility updates required by the fielding of these modifications.

 MC2S Block 08 modifications include but are not limited to: 1) Communication system upgrades; 2) Mission and support asset upgrades; 3) Cyber security modernization; 4) Network upgrades; 5) Environmental
 and Filtration system upgrades along with and including initial spares and test facility updates required by the fielding of these modifications. Due to the limited spares demand rate and indefinite system lifespan,
 Life of Type buys may be required to support weapon system modifications across the active MC2S Block Programs. Additionally, program will fund PMA support for the MC2S Block 08 program. PMA costs fund
 acquisition support strategy as well as engineering and technical expertise associated with procurement activities. In addition, PMA costs will also support equipment test, travel, and other program related costs
 associated with install of procurement equipment. Funding for this effort is in Program Element 0305903F and is funded under IAW full funding policy. Block 08 is a continuation of Block 07.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Air Force                                                                                                                Date: April 2026
