 program equips U.S. Air Force (USAF) Active Duty, Air National Guard, and Air Force Reserve flying units with hardware required for mission planning and airdrop operations.

 1. MPS HARDWARE: Equips USAF operational flying units with hardware required to perform mission planning and integrate information with aircraft data transfer device systems. Aircraft supported include:

 Air Combat Command (ACC): F-15, F-16, F-22, F-35, A-10, E-3, E-4, E-7, RC/OC-135, HH-60, HC-130, EC-130, U-2, RQ-4

