INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3080_L041$$, 2027, $$PE 0208087F Distributed Cyber Warfare Operations (DCWO)
 Provides for the innovation, test, support, and deployment of cyberspace solutions in the form of materiel and non-materiel capabilities in support of USAF offensive cyberspace operations (OCO) to include but
 not limited to USAF OCO units, Combatant Commands (COCOMs), and other authorized agencies. Funding procures specialized hardware and software necessary for associated infrastructure and capability
 deployment across multiple OCO mission areas. Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0208087F.

 PE 0208088F AF Defensive Cyberspace Operations (DCO)
 AF DCO procures commercial off the shelf (COTS) hardware for the Integrated Defensive Cyberspace System (IDCS). IDCS hardware is configured as mobile or fixed form factors. Mobile hardware is used
 to equip Mission Defense Teams (MDTs) and Air Force retained Cyber Protection Teams (CPTs). Fixed hardware is deployed to all 188 Department of the Air Force (DAF) bases to collect network logs and
 serve as critical nodes in the IDCS architecture providing situational awareness of the key cyberspace terrain essential to the projection of Air Power. Operational users of IDCS include USAF operational units
 -- predominantly Sixteenth Air Force (AFCYBER), 688th Cyber Security Service Provider (CSSP), and 67th Cyber Wing, Air Force CPTs, MDTs, and network defenders. The capabilities provided will process
 data from and protect USAF networks and systems at multiple classification levels. Funding also provides IDCS software components essential to protecting Department of War (DoW) network enclaves, mission/
 weapon systems and control systems against unauthorized intrusion, exploitation, corruption, and/or destruction. Continued procurement and deployment of IDCS hardware and software will help meet the urgent
 need to deploy modernized, interconnected cyber defenses to deter near-peer aggression. AF DCO provides the DAF increased mission assurance through enhanced cyber defense and situational awareness
 over the systems and assets required to enable the movement of forces and employment of US Air Power. Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0208088F.

 PE 0804762F Cyberspace Training and Ranges
 Cyberspace Training and Ranges provides solutions in the form of material and non-material cyberspace training platforms, threat representative networks, mission relevant cyber terrain, and multi-domain
 architecture to support training and exercises for DoW and AF cyber operations. This includes initial/mission qualification training (IQT/MQT), mission rehearsals, and exercises to support USAF Offensive and
 Defensive Cyber Operations and Network Operations units, Combatant Commands, and other authorized agencies. Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0804762F.

