INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3080_L041$$, 2026, $$PE 0208076F Mission Defense Team (MDT)
 MDT program increases resiliency and survivability of Air Force Major Weapon systems and infrastructure critical to the execution of AF core missions utilizing Core functions conducted by Mission Assurance
 Cyber Coordination Element (MACCE), Functional communities, and 16AF support with the objectives to break the adversaries kill chain, provide decision advantage for the warfighters, and increase military
 lethality. The MACCE are essential for maintaining high-end readiness and mission assurance ensuring the Air Force's ability to de-fend its weapon systems and infrastructure against evolving threats.

 PE 0208087F Distributed Cyber Warfare Operations (DCWO)
 DCWO provides for the innovation, test, support, and deployment of cyberspace solutions in the form of materiel and non-materiel capabilities in support of USAF offensive cyberspace operations (OCO) to
 include but not limited to USAF OCO units, Combatant Commands (COCOMs), and other authorized agencies. Funding procures specialized hardware and software necessary for associated infrastructure and
 capability deployment across multiple OCO mission areas. Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0208087F.

 PE 0208088F Air Force (AF) Defensive Cyberspace Operations (DCO)
 AF DCO procures commercial off the shelf (COTS) hardware for the Integrated Defensive Cyberspace System (IDCS). IDCS hardware is configured in mobile and fixed form factors. Mobile hardware is
 used to equip Mission Defense Teams (MDTs) and AF retained Cyber Protection Teams (CPTs). Fixed hardware is deployed to all 188 DAF bases to collect network logs and serve as critical node in the
 IDCS architecture providing situational awareness of the key cyberspace terrain essential to the projection of Air Power. Operational users of IDCS include USAF operational units -- predominantly Sixteenth
 AF (AFCYBER), 688th Cyber Security Service Provider (CSSP), and 67th Cyber Wing, AF CPTs, MDTs, and network defenders. The capabilities provided will process data from and protect USAF networks
 and systems at multiple classification levels. Funding also provides IDCS software components essential to protecting Department of Defense (DoD) network enclaves, mission/weapon systems and control
 systems against unauthorized intrusion, exploitation, corruption, and/or destruction. Continued procurement and deployment of IDCS hardware and software will help meet the urgent need to deploy modernized,
 interconnected cyber defenses to deter near-peer aggression. AF DCO contributes to successful sortie generation (getting our planes off the ground and keeping them in the fight) while ensuring the integrity and
 global dominance of US Air Power. Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0208088F.

 PE 0303166F Joint Information Operations Range (JIOR)
 JIOR provides the DoD with a closed network that forms a global live-fire information operations range complex. JIOR uses encrypted tunneling over existing transport networks to conduct mission rehearsal,
 training, testing, concept development, and experimentation in support of Information Operations (IO), Electronic Warfare (EW), Offensive Cyber Operations (OCO), Defensive Cyber Operations (DCO), Spectrum
 Warfare, Space Operations, and Special Operations Forces mission areas in a realistic threat representative environment. JIOR provides the capability to train and certify Cyber Mission Forces (CMFs) on the$$, NULL, $${"bucket":"fy26_specific_pb_v43","method":"direct_li_with_title_overlap","rapidfuzz_score":100.0,"src_li":41,"src_title":"C3 Countermeasures","supersedes":"fy26_pointing_at_fy27_pb_placeholder","applied_at":"2026-05-09T_v196b"}$$, $$Budget J-Books/FY26/USAF/FY26 Air Force Other Procurement.pdf$$, 461, 461, $$f0e33f105652b647$$, $$2026-05-10T02:12:16.956197+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3080_L044$$, 2026, $$DEAMS, an Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) program built upon the commercial-off-the-shelf (COTS) solution Oracle e-Business Suite (EBS), provides a modern accounting and finance management
 capability with robust auditability at its core. As the Department of the Air Force's (DAF) existing core accounting and financial management solution, DEAMS represents a key component of the DAF's long-term
 business process improvements, addressing the Secretary of Defense's (SECDEF) priority for auditability and is the essential tool for ensuring the DAF's alignment with the SECDEF's vision for a more efficient
 and effective military. By providing accurate financial data, strengthening internal controls, and facilitating auditability, DEAMS empowers the DAF to meet its financial reporting obligations, maintain public trust,
 and ultimately contribute to a stronger national defense.

 Additionally, this program element uses critical financial data to enhance future program planning and execution and will provide greater transparency to defense spending, making it easier to track how funds are
 being used and identify potential areas for savings. This increased accountability aligns with the SECDEF's call for a clean Pentagon audit and ensures the responsible use of taxpayer dollars.

 FY2026 funding will support continued capability development and functionalities within the system. This includes ongoing efforts to achieve an unqualified System and Organization Controls (SOC) audit
 opinion, ensuring compliance with audit and transparency requirements. Funding will also enhance data integrity and automation by evolving the Treasury Direct Disburse (TDD) capability to streamline interfund
 transactions. System integration and interoperability will be improved by integrating Acquisition Management System (AMS) and Foreign Military Sales (FMS) accounting systems with DEAMS for improved
 financial visibility and reconciliation. Funding will also be used to modernize technology by upgrading the Oracle e-Business Suite (EBS) and the Oracle Analytic Server (OAS). These upgrades will enhance
 system performance, security, and scalability, enabling DEAMS to remain a relevant and auditable accounting system.

 The FY2026 funding also supports the development of the system by continuing to enhance the functionality of the logistics, payroll, asset accounting, budget distribution and personnel travel management
 systems creating an enterprise-wide system for seamless data flow and better tracking of resources and more accurate financial reporting.

 This program element replaces numerous inefficient and/or obsolete legacy systems with a single, integrated platform that standardizes financial data across the DAF. The streamlined approach ensures data
 consistency and accuracy, critical for reliable financial reporting and informed decision-making.

 This program element supports the current 17,000 users across all United States Air Force (USAF) and United States Space Force (USSF) bases worldwide, serving all Air Force and Space Force Major
 Commands, and Unified Commands where the DAF acts as the executive agent. The DAF will deploy DEAMS to the acquisition community to include acquisition program executive offices, laboratories, test
 centers, and air logistics complexes. These deployments will add an additional 4,500 users for a total of 21,500 users.$$, NULL, $${"bucket":"fy26_specific_pb_v43","method":"direct_li_with_title_overlap","rapidfuzz_score":100.0,"src_li":44,"src_title":"Defense Enterprise Accounting & Mgt Sys","supersedes":"fy26_pointing_at_fy27_pb_placeholder","applied_at":"2026-05-09T_v196b"}$$, $$Budget J-Books/FY26/USAF/FY26 Air Force Other Procurement.pdf$$, 485, 485, $$07b5e4fa2553a5b9$$, $$2026-05-10T02:12:16.956197+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3080_L050$$, 2027, $$BASE INFORMATION TRANSPORT INFRASTRUCTURE (BITI) procures base-level network infrastructure (e.g., routers, switches, access points, controllers, cables, and other IT-networking equipment /
 infrastructure components) for unclassified and classified Air Force intranet communications. Base Infrastructure Modernization (BIM), under the BITI Program Element (PE), delivers base-level Air Force
 cyberspace network and integrated information infrastructure for DAF installations (active duty, reserve, and Air National Guard (ANG)) and associated Geographically Separated Units (GSU) at approved
 locations. The BIM portion of the BITI PE encompasses base-level information transport systems, both Air Force Network (AFNET) non-secure intranet protocol router (NIPR) / secure intranet protocol router
 (SIPR) wired and wireless network, supporting base mission requirements for digital voice, data, and video systems. This includes commercial device connectivity, Unified Capabilities (UC), and the management
 systems necessary to manage, protect, and maintain DAF battle networks.

 BIM: Designs, procures, and delivers a modernized, commercial best-practice Enterprise Information Technology as a Service (EITaaS) network. This network provides a comprehensive, holistic wired and
 wireless BAN infrastructure, including inside and outside cabling, for the AFNet NIPR and SIPR. This supports the base-level Air and Space Force cyberspace network and integrated information infrastructure
 for DAF installations (Active Duty, Reserve, and ANG) and associated GSUs at approved locations. BIM supports the DAF initiative to utilize an EITaaS model for IT network operations, maintenance, and
 sustainment. BIM provides base network infrastructure to remediate current bandwidth and performance issues (improving user experience) DAF-wide. This supports growing Service IT demands and
 requirements for the AFNet NIPR and SIPR networks. BIM increases data-to-decision speeds, which is foundational to supporting emerging mission communication requirements.

 The FY2027 funding enables the modernization of 187 Active Duty, Space Force, Reserve, and Air National Guard main operating bases and associated GSUs including the procurement and installation of
 equipment upgrading the AFNET NIPR/SIPR wired and wireless base-level IT infrastructure. BIM modernization includes sustainment through communications squadron manpower augmentation, directly
 supporting the DAF's transition to EITaaS.

 In accordance with Section 1815 of the FY 2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110-181), this item is necessary for use by the active and reserve components of the armed forces for homeland defense
 missions, domestic emergency responses, and providing military support to civil authorities.

 Funding for this exhibit is contained in PE 0303004F.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Air Force                                                                                                               Date: April 2026
