INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3080_L050$$, 2026, $$BASE INFORMATION TRANSPORT INFRASTRUCTURE (BITI), formerly known as INFORMATION TRANSPORT SYSTEM (ITS): BITI procures base-level network infrastructure (e.g., routers, switches, access
 points, controllers, cables, and other IT-networking equipment) for unclassified and classified Air Force intranet communications. The FY2026 funding enables the procurement and installation of equipment
 to upgrade the wired and wireless base-level IT network infrastructure. This Base Infrastructure Modernization (BIM) approach upgrades the Base Area Network (BAN) equipment directly supporting the DAF's
 transition to Enterprise Information Technology as a Service (EITaaS).

 The FY2025-FY2026 funding decrease is driven by the completion of initial BIM efforts focusing on Active Duty PACAF and Air National Guard locations. BIM, under the BITI Program Element (PE), delivers
 base-level Air Force cyberspace network and integrated information infrastructure for DAF installations (active duty, reserve, and Air National Guard (ANG)) and Geographically Separated Units (GSU) at
 approved locations. The BIM portion of the BITI PE encompasses base-level information transport systems, both wired and wireless, to support base requirements for digital voice, data, and video systems.
 This includes commercial device connectivity, Unified Capabilities (UC), and the management systems necessary to manage, protect, and maintain Air and Space Forces networks. BITI provides a robust and
 secure infrastructure incorporating high-availability and multi-tiered network connections at ACC approved facilities supporting Airmen and Guardians. The efforts in this program budget line fund the deployment,
 upkeep, and continuous support of vital information transport systems across the Air and Space Forces. These efforts, combined with other DAF battle network IT initiatives, deliver technological advancements
 such as datacenter consolidation, cloud-based services, and mobile computing. BITI ensures operating locations have the required infrastructure, bandwidth, and overall network capabilities supporting current
 and future NIPR/SIPR communication requirements of the DAF warfighters.

 BIM: Designs, procures, and delivers a modernized, commercial best-practice Enterprise IT as a Service (EITaaS) network. This network provides a comprehensive, holistic wired and wireless Base Area
 Network (BAN) infrastructure, including inside and outside cabling, for the Air Force Network (AFNet) NIPR and SIPR. This supports the base-level Air and Space Force cyberspace network and integrated
 information infrastructure for DAF installations (active duty, reserve, and ANG) and GSUs at ACC Lead Command approved locations. BIM supports the DAF initiative to utilize an EITaaS model for IT network
 operations, maintenance, and sustainment. BIM provides base network infrastructure to remediate current bandwidth and performance issues (improving user experience) DAF-wide. This supports growing
 Service IT demands and requirements for the AFNet NIPR and SIPR networks. BIM increases data-to-decision speeds, which is foundational to supporting emerging mission communication requirements. These
 requirements include the Flight Line of the Future (FLoF), Operational Imperatives, Advanced Battle Management Systems (ABMS), and Combined Joint All-Domain Command and Control (CJADC2).

 In accordance with Section 1815 of the FY 2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110-181), this item is necessary for use by the active and reserve components of the armed forces for homeland defense
 missions, domestic emergency responses, and providing military support to civil authorities.$$, NULL, $${"bucket":"fy26_specific_pb_v43","method":"direct_li_with_title_overlap","rapidfuzz_score":100.0,"src_li":50,"src_title":"Base Information Transpt Infrast (BITI) Wired","supersedes":"fy26_pointing_at_fy27_pb_placeholder","applied_at":"2026-05-09T_v196b"}$$, $$Budget J-Books/FY26/USAF/FY26 Air Force Other Procurement.pdf$$, 517, 517, $$96d677758896d0ae$$, $$2026-05-10T02:12:16.956197+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3080_L051$$, 2026, $$These programs support Cyberspace Activities

 Air Force Network (AFNET) provides Commercial Off-The-Shelf (COTS) solutions to implement, deliver, and upgrade the IT equipment and technology (e.g., firewalls, routers, servers etc.) that constitutes the Air
 Force's wide area network (WAN). The systems procured in this budget line provide the equipment and technology for Air Force Information Network Operations (AFINOps), which includes technology for network
 defense. This program includes the defense in depth cybersecurity capabilities critical to protecting AFNET data and the Air Force strategic entry points into the DoD Information Network (DODIN).

 AFNET is on track to complete the initial NIPR Installation Service Node (ISN) effort and the Next Generation Gateway Component Enterprise Data Center (CEDC) effort. Other projects include installation
 processing nodes, Information Management Suite (IMS), SIPRNet C2 Nodes, Dual Path Resiliency (DPR) base boundary upgrades, enterprise network security, network situational awareness and C2
 capabilities. These projects allow for the interface with and assured movement of information from terrestrial, air and space-based networks, thus enabling Air Force Information Operations (AFINOps). All funds
 used for AFNET Systems support the continued establishment and transformation of the AFINOps construct toward DoD standards and specifications

 The procurement efforts in this program budget line include, but are not limited to, system equipment, engineering/integration, certification and accreditation, deployment, testing, training equipment/systems,
 associated training and interim contractor support. All activities may incorporate support to other program elements across the Air Force Information Enterprise in accordance with SAF/CIO direction.

 FY26 request was reduced by $.426M for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration in alignment with Executive Order 14222, implementing the
 President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiatives.

 PE 0303089F, CYBERSPACE OPERATIONS SYSTEMS

 This PE executes requirements for both AFINC and CSCS weapon systems. Funds may be used for other AFNET requirements if required.

 (1) AIR FORCE INTRANET CONTROL (AFINC): Procures and installs equipment for network operations, network defense and overall management of the AFNET Gateways (GWs), the Information Management
 Suite (IMS) and the base Service Delivery Point Routers as well as the Air Force discrete requirements associated with AFNET cybersecurity and will implement in accordance with Zero Trust principles.$$, NULL, $${"bucket":"fy26_specific_pb_v43","method":"direct_li_with_title_overlap","rapidfuzz_score":100.0,"src_li":51,"src_title":"AFNET","supersedes":"fy26_pointing_at_fy27_pb_placeholder","applied_at":"2026-05-09T_v196b"}$$, $$Budget J-Books/FY26/USAF/FY26 Air Force Other Procurement.pdf$$, 525, 525, $$ac72e57479204420$$, $$2026-05-10T02:12:16.956197+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3080_L051$$, 2027, $$PE 0303089F, CYBERSPACE OPERATIONS SYSTEMS

 Air Force Network (AFNET) provides Commercial Off-The-Shelf (COTS) solutions to implement, deliver, and upgrade the information technology (IT) equipment and technology (e.g., firewalls, routers, servers
 etc.) that constitutes the Air Force's Wide Area Network (WAN). The systems procured in this budget line provide the equipment and technology for Air Force Information Network Operations (AFINOps), which
 includes technology for network defense. This program includes the defense in depth cybersecurity capabilities critical to protecting Air Force Information Network (AFIN) data and the Air Force strategic entry
 points into the DoD Information Network (DODIN).

 This PE executes requirements for both Air Force Intranet Control (AFINC) and Cyberspace Security and Control System (CSCS) weapon systems. Funds may be used for other AFNET requirements if required.

 (1) AIR FORCE INTRANET CONTROL (AFINC): Procures and installs equipment for network operations, network defense and overall management of the AFNET Gateways (GWs), the Information Management
 Suite (IMS) and the base Service Delivery Point Routers as well as the Air Force discrete requirements associated with AFNET cybersecurity and will implement in accordance with Zero Trust principles.

 (2) CYBERSPACE SECURITY AND CONTROL SYSTEM (CSCS): Procures, installs, and hosts capabilities contributing to cyber mission assurance, including proactive defense and persistent network
 operations for the Air Force, the Air Force-provisioned portions of the DoD Information Network (DoDIN), and the Air Force Information Network (AFIN). CSCS modifications support the following activities:
 fault resolution to maintain operational capabilities; lead-in coordination activities at base-level Network Control Centers for necessary network security actions; monitoring of AF network services; managing of
 boundary protection devices and the Air Force network infrastructure; and continuous network situational awareness.

 The procurement efforts in this program budget line include, but are not limited to, system equipment, engineering/integration, certification and accreditation, deployment, testing, training equipment/systems,
 associated training and interim contractor support. All activities may incorporate support to other program elements across the Air Force Information Enterprise in accordance with Secretary of the Air Force, Chief
 Information Officer's direction.

 In accordance with Section 1815 of the FY 2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110-181), this item is necessary for use by the active and reserve components of the Armed Forces for homeland
 defense missions, domestic emergency responses, and providing military support to civil authorities.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Air Force                                                                                                                Date: April 2026
