INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3080_L051_v21$$, 2027, $$PE 0303133F HIGH FREQUENCY GLOBAL COMMUNICATIONS SYSTEM (HFGCS)
 The High Frequency Global Communications System (HFGCS) program provides the Department of War (DoW) with a critical unique strategic asset: a global, high-power, high-frequency (HF) network. This
 network ensures resilient communication for both nuclear and non-nuclear command and control (NC3/C2), serving a wide range of users, including US Strategic Command (USSTRATCOM), Air Mobility
 Command, the White House Communications Agency, Navy submariner forces, and other government agencies like the Department of Homeland Security and the Federal Emergency Management Agency
 (FEMA).

 HFGCS is essential for disseminating critical information to global strategic forces, especially in contested environments where satellite communications might be compromised. The program leverages a network
 of 13 strategically located ground stations and two network control stations equipped with modern, commercially based, HF radio technology, ensuring beyond-line-of-sight communication with aircraft, ships, and
 land-based platforms.

 Procurement funding focuses on modernizing and maintaining this vital system by replacing outdated audio switching equipment, mitigating obsolescence issues, and enhancing cybersecurity. These upgrades
 will ensure HFGCS remains a reliable and resilient communication backbone for the DoW and its partners.

 Specifically, this funding supports six key modernization lines of effort: improving Arctic C2, implementing robust HF waveforms across the DoW, supporting Air Force HF modernization efforts, integrating
 Air Operations Center HF requirements, implementing a robust Pacific Air Forces (PACAF) HF strategy for the US Indo-Pacific Command (INDOPACOM) area of responsibility (AOR), and executing NC3 HF
 modernization. Additionally, it covers Direct Mission Support/Program Support Costs (DMS/PMA), System Engineering, Joint Interoperability Test Center (JITC) installation testing, and shipping.

 This funding also prioritizes the acquisition of controlled, critical protection items classified as essential military communication equipment. Funding may be used to address Diminishing Manufacturing Sources
 (DMS) issues.

 Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0303133F

